  "reportSummary": "Retrospective SENTINEL analysis of the 2015 Gold King Mine spill demonstrates detection capability within ~2 hours of the breach, compared to the 24+ hours it took for EPA confirmation. The catastrophic pH crash (7.8 to 2.1), conductivity spike (280 to 8500 uS/cm), and characteristic orange turbidity plume provided unmistakable sensor signatures. Source attribution identified acid mine drainage at 95% confidence within 1 hour. The Digital Biosentinel predicted near-complete aquatic mortality, consistent with observed fish kills across 100+ miles of river. This case exemplifies SENTINEL's value for rapid industrial contamination response.",
